# Header + Wallet + Reown Rules

## Core Rule

Header must be Astro-first, static, SEO-friendly, and extremely lightweight.

Do not load Reown, Solana wallet libraries, Solana SDK, wallet adapters, or any wallet provider globally.

Public header must render meaningful HTML without JavaScript.

Initial page load must not include:
- `@reown/appkit`
- `@reown/appkit-adapter-solana`
- `@solana/web3.js`
- `@solana/wallet-adapter-react`
- `@solana/wallet-adapter-wallets`
- `@solana/wallet-adapter-react-ui`
- wallet provider code
- global wallet modal code

Wallet code must load only after the user intentionally clicks the wallet button.

## Header Architecture

Header must be an Astro component:

```txt
src/components/layout/Header.astro
```

Header may contain only:
- logo
- main navigation links
- static desktop nav
- static CTA links if needed
- lightweight wallet trigger placeholder
- optional theme/network display only if implemented without heavy JS

Header must not be a React component.

Do not create:

```txt
Header.tsx
WalletHeader.tsx
GlobalWalletProvider.tsx
ReownProvider.tsx
```

Do not wrap app/layout with wallet providers.

Bad:

```tsx
<WalletProvider>
  <Header />
  <main>{children}</main>
</WalletProvider>
```

Good:

```astro
<Header />
<main>
  <slot />
</main>
```

## Header HTML Requirements

Header must be fully visible and useful in raw HTML.

`view-source:` must show:
- logo link
- main navigation links
- important internal links
- wallet button placeholder text
- no JS dependency for basic navigation comprehension

Header stays Astro. Only wallet button area may be a tiny island.

## Wallet Button Rule

Wallet button must be a small React island.

Allowed file:

```txt
src/islands/wallet/WalletConnectButton.tsx
```

The wallet island must render a lightweight button initially.

It must not initialize Reown on mount.

Bad:

```tsx
import { createAppKit } from '@reown/appkit';

const modal = createAppKit(...);
```

Good:

```tsx
async function handleConnect() {
  const { openWalletModal } = await import('@/lib/wallet/reown-client');
  await openWalletModal();
}
```

Reown must load only inside click handlers.

## Reown Lazy Loading Rule

Create a dedicated lazy module:

```txt
src/lib/wallet/reown-client.ts
```

This is the only file allowed to import Reown packages.

Allowed imports only inside this file:

```ts
import { createAppKit } from '@reown/appkit';
import { SolanaAdapter } from '@reown/appkit-adapter-solana';
```

No other file may import Reown directly.

Module must use singleton initialization.

Important:
- never initialize Reown at module top-level
- never initialize Reown in layout
- never initialize Reown in `Header.astro`
- never initialize Reown in Astro frontmatter
- never initialize Reown on page load

## Wallet Button UI Behavior

Before connection:

```txt
Connect Wallet
```

Contextual action-page copy is allowed, for example:
- Connect Wallet to Create Token
- Connect Wallet to Mint Token
- Connect Wallet to Burn Token
- Connect Wallet to Revoke Authority

After connection, show shortened address:

```txt
7xK4...9Qa2
```

Do not block forms until wallet connects.

Bad:
- hide form until wallet connects
- require wallet to view fields
- require header wallet before page interaction

Good:
- page content visible
- form visible
- fields fillable
- wallet required only for final transaction action

## Header Wallet Hydration

Use least aggressive hydration:

Preferred:

```astro
<WalletConnectButton client:idle />
```

If immediate clickability is required:

```astro
<WalletConnectButton client:load />
```

For public pages, prefer:

```astro
<WalletConnectButton client:visible />
```

or

```astro
<WalletConnectButton client:idle />
```

Do not convert entire header to React because of wallet button.

## Mobile Header Rule

Desktop header must remain static Astro HTML.

Mobile menu should be:
1. CSS-only where practical
2. tiny React island only for open/close state when necessary

Allowed:

```txt
src/islands/navigation/MobileMenuToggle.tsx
```

Not allowed:
- Reown logic inside mobile menu
- full React mobile navigation
- wallet providers in drawer
- Solana SDK imports for menu state
- animation libraries (including Framer Motion)

Use CSS-only transitions only if needed.

## Network Selector Rule

Network selector must not load Solana SDK.

Allowed values:

```txt
mainnet
devnet
testnet
```

Persist with:
- `localStorage`
- cookie

Do not store:
- Solana `Connection` objects
- wallet adapter objects
- Reown instances
- transaction objects

## Theme Toggle Rule

Theme toggle must stay tiny and independent from wallet state.

Allowed:
- inline script to set `html.dark`
- localStorage theme persistence
- tiny island if needed

Do not use global React theme providers.

## Global Provider Rule

Do not create global provider stacks for layout/wallet/theme.

Forbidden pattern:

```tsx
<AppProviders>
  <ThemeProvider>
    <WalletProvider>
      <ReownProvider>{children}</ReownProvider>
    </WalletProvider>
  </ThemeProvider>
</AppProviders>
```

Allowed:
- static Astro layout
- isolated islands
- lazy wallet initialization
- simple localStorage/cookie preferences

## Environment Variables

Frontend may only use public-safe variables:

```env
PUBLIC_SITE_URL=
PUBLIC_REOWN_PROJECT_ID=
PUBLIC_DEFAULT_NETWORK=
PUBLIC_DXRA_CORE_API_URL=
```

Forbidden in frontend:

```env
RPC_PRIVATE_URL=
HELIUS_API_KEY=
PINATA_JWT=
JITO_PRIVATE_CONFIG=
SERVER_SECRET=
PRIVATE_RPC_ENDPOINT=
```

Never expose private RPC URLs or private API keys in wallet config.

## File Structure

Use:

```txt
src/
├─ components/
│  └─ layout/
│     ├─ Header.astro
│     ├─ Footer.astro
│     └─ Sidebar.astro
├─ islands/
│  ├─ wallet/
│  │  └─ WalletConnectButton.tsx
│  └─ navigation/
│     └─ MobileMenuToggle.tsx
├─ lib/
│  └─ wallet/
│     ├─ reown-client.ts
│     ├─ wallet-state.ts
│     └─ format-wallet-address.ts
└─ styles/
   └─ global.css
```

## Accessibility Rules

Header must include:

```html
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
```

Wallet trigger must be a real button:

```html
<button type="button">
```

Mobile menu button must include:
- `aria-expanded`
- `aria-controls`
- `aria-label`

Do not use clickable divs for controls.

## Bundle Verification Rules

After implementation, verify:
- initial JS bundle excludes Reown
- initial JS bundle excludes Solana SDK
- initial JS bundle excludes wallet-adapter packages
- header is not bundled as a large React component
- navigation links are visible in `view-source`
- wallet code appears only in lazy chunks

Search build output for:

```txt
@reown
@solana
wallet-adapter
web3.js
spl-token
```

If any of these appear in initial public page bundle, implementation is incorrect.

## Final Acceptance Checklist

- Header is Astro, not React
- Navigation links render in HTML
- Logo renders in HTML
- Wallet button is isolated as tiny island
- Reown loads only after wallet button click
- No global wallet provider
- No Reown import in layout/header/sidebar/footer
- No Solana SDK in initial bundle
- Mobile menu is CSS-only or tiny island
- Forms remain visible before wallet connection
- Wallet required only for final transaction action
- Build passes
- Lighthouse/PageSpeed is not degraded by wallet code

## TL;DR

```txt
Header = Astro static HTML
Wallet button = tiny React island
Reown = dynamic import only after click
No global provider
No wallet code in initial bundle
No Solana SDK in header/layout
```
